---
description: Always use DDEV in this repository
alwaysApply: true
---

- This repository uses ddev as the required local development environment.
- Always run repository commands through ddev when they depend on the project runtime, services, PHP extensions, Composer dependencies, or the database.
- Always run PHP commands via ddev exec php ....
- Prefer ddev exec composer ... for Composer operations that must run inside the container.
- Prefer ddev exec php vendor/bin/phpunit ... for tests.
- If ddev is not running yet, start it first with ddev start.
- Do not default to host-level php or composer commands in this repository.